{"id":25142,"date":"2017-08-09T12:50:41","date_gmt":"2017-08-09T08:50:41","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=25142"},"modified":"2019-05-25T09:38:21","modified_gmt":"2019-05-25T05:38:21","slug":"salman-silence-anger","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/08\/09\/salman-silence-anger\/","title":{"rendered":"Salman on Silence: Speak truth or be silent, do not be angry"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Maymun ibn Mihran reported: A man came to Salman al-Farisi, may Allah be pleased with him, and he said, \u201cO Abu Abdullah, advise me.\u201d Salman said, \u201cDo not speak.\u201d The man said, \u201cHow can one live among people and not speak?\u201d Salman said, \u201cIf you speak, speak the truth or be silent.\u201d The man said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d Salman said, \u201cDo not be angry.\u201d The man said, \u201cYou have commanded me not to be angry, yet it overcomes me in a way I cannot control.\u201d Salman said, \u201cIf you are angry, restrain your tongue and your hand.\u201d The man said, \u201cTell me more.\u201d Salman said, \u201cDo not mix with people.\u201d The man said, \u201cHow can one live among people and not mix with them?\u201d Salman said, \u201cIf you mix with people, speak truthfully and fulfill the trust.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: al-\u1e62amt li Ibn Ab\u012b Duny\u0101 610<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0645\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0645\u064f\u0648\u0646\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u0650\u0647\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u062c\u064e\u0627\u0621\u064e \u0631\u064e\u062c\u064f\u0644\u064c \u0625\u0650\u0644\u064e\u0649 \u0633\u064e\u0644\u0652\u0645\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0627 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u064e\u0627 